projectInfo.name: Bangladesh Refugee Crisis camp mapping - Shamlapur camp
projectInfo.shortDescription: Almost 1 million Rohingya refugees have fled Myanmar for Southeast Bangladesh in the past few months. CartONG is supporting several humanitarian organizations, in particular UNHCR and the Inter Sector Coordination Group,  in mapping the camp to support the humanitarian response to the crisis.
projectInfo.description:
Almost 1 million Rohingya refugees have fled Myanmar for Southeast Bangladesh in the past few months. CartONG is supporting several humanitarian organizations, in particular UNHCR and the Inter Sector Coordination Group,  in mapping the camp to support the humanitarian response to the crisis.

This project covers a new area of the camp, making use of the new drone imagery produce by IOM to map the shelters. Thanks to them for sharing it openly!
projectInfo.instructions:
Imagery details
=======
The mapping will be done using the drone imagery produced on 2018-01-25 by the International Organization for Migrations.

**The mapping previously done have been traced based on a less accurate satellite imagery, you should therefore update the data to fit the drone imagery if you see new existing elements. Please start mapping the priority area corresponding to the new camp, and then update the remaining area.**

Tasks around the edge of this project do not have updated drone imagery, they can just be marked as "Bad Imagery" no need to map them as they have already been mapped.


Buildings
=======
The buildings in the camps may be a mixture of formal (bricks, concrete etc) and informal (tarpaulins, huts, etc.) constructions. 

Some photo examples: [large tarpaulin shelters within the formal camp](https://www.flickr.com/photos/154760933@N07/36396024293/) or [makeshift huts thatched with vegetation in the informal settlements](https://www.flickr.com/photos/unhcr/3095082377/).

Please map all of these structures using the tags below:
* In the ID editor: label the area as “Building” then correct for right angles with the “S” key

* In JOSM: from the Tags/Memberships window, click “Add” and use the tag *building=yes*; then correct for right angles using the “Q” key 
* Or using plugin building in JOSM

**The long blocks of several shelters should be divided in individual shelters (usually per 6).**
If you are using JOSM, you can **use the terracer plugin** which allows you to draw the whole extent of the building and then split it into x parts (mainly 6 here).

![Example](http://www.cartong.org/sites/cartong/files/Capture%20d%E2%80%99e%CC%81cran%202018-01-12%20a%CC%80%2014.05.18.png)

Do not stick building with roads. Do not hesitate to delete buildings that are not existing anymore.

Roads & paths will be completed separately by experienced mappers, please only map them if you have already done road mapping in this crisis' context.
